Hi!

I'm trying to migrate from Ramda to lodash and I'm using `_.curry` on a function composed with `_.flowRight` but it doesn't work:

``` js
const add5 = (a, b) => a + 5;
const sub = (a, b) => b - a;

const subPlus5 = _.flowRight(add5, sub);
console.log(subPlus5(50, 100)); // 100 - 50 + 5

const curriedSubPlus5 = _.curry(subPlus5);
const sub50Plus5 = curriedSubPlus5(50);
console.log(sub50Plus5(100)); // should log 55 but shows "sub50Plus5 is not a function"
```

Here is a jsbin: https://jsbin.com/qerasi/69/edit?js,console

It does work if I use the function arity parameter of `_.curry`:

``` js
const curriedSubPlus5 = _.curry(subPlus5, 2);
const sub50Plus5 = curriedSubPlus5(50);
console.log(sub50Plus5(100)); // logs "55"
```

(https://jsbin.com/qerasi/80/edit?js,console)

It also works if I use the Ramda `R.compose` function instead of `_.flowRight`: https://jsbin.com/qerasi/81/edit?js,console

I wanted to know if lodash will support this use case of curried composed functions or do I have to use the `arity` paramter of `_.curry`?

