Example situation, reuse of the same throttled function in different contexts:

``` js
const log = throttle(console.log.bind(console), 1000);
AA.onscroll = log;
B.onscroll = log;
C.onscroll = log;
D.onscroll = log;

///

AA.scrollTo(0, 3); //--> "event {...}"
AA.scrollTo(0, 3); //--> no log // ok!
B.scrollTo(0, 6); //--> no log // not ok
C.scrollTo(0, 3); //--> no log // not ok
D.scrollTo(0, 6); //--> no log // not ok
```

Ideal solution, like with memoize's resolver:

``` js
const log = throttle(console.log.bind(console), 1000, {
  resolver: e => e.currentTarget
});
AA.onscroll = log;
B.onscroll = log;
C.onscroll = log;
D.onscroll = log;

///

AA.scrollTo(0, 3); //--> "event {...}"
AA.scrollTo(0, 3); //--> no log // ok!
B.scrollTo(0, 6); //--> "event {...}"
C.scrollTo(0, 3); //--> "event {...}"
D.scrollTo(0, 6); //--> "event {...}"
```

Current solution:

``` js
AA.onscroll = throttle(console.log.bind(console), 1000);
B.onscroll = throttle(console.log.bind(console), 1000);
C.onscroll = throttle(console.log.bind(console), 1000);
D.onscroll = throttle(console.log.bind(console), 1000);

